The rooms are spacious and beds very comfortable, unfortunately there was no bottled water in the room which was disappointing given the hotel standard but this is my only downside of the stay.	The room itself was up to Marriott's usual standards - well done, not over-the-top luxurious, but very nice.	The room was a standard hotel room, nothing special or unique.	We had connecting rooms, these were prepared to a very high standard, house keeping do a first class job in this hotel.	The room was like any standard 4 star hotel room.